<content type="str">Gerald R. (Jerry) Wald passed peacefully on Jan. 18, 2017. 
Born Dec. 31, 1932, in Carbondale, Pa., to Ira and Goldie Wald, Jerry attended Carbondale High School and Penn State University before joining the Army. After his service, Jerry earned a bachelor&apos;s degree in electrical engineering from Temple University. In 1959, he married Patricia (Pat) Ann Moffitt, the love of his life, who blessed him with four children. The family lived in New York before moving to Saratoga, Calif. Jerry worked for Link flight simulation company. After retiring, Jerry and Pat moved to Sun City Lincoln Hills, Calif., where they enjoyed golfing, traveling, spending time with friends and supporting the San Francisco Giants and 49ers. 

Jerry will be greatly missed by Pat, his wife of 57 years; their four children, twins Mark and Debbie, Jerry Jr. and Susan; and 11 grandchildren and nine great-grandchildren. 

There will be a celebration of life, 11 a.m., Feb. 8, 2017, at Orchard Creek Lodge, Sun City Lincoln Hills. In lieu of flowers, the family requests donations be made in Jerry&apos;s name to the cancer  .</content> 
